cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC 

The paper deals with computer vision and graphics, specifically with the problem of projecting 360-degree panoramas with fewer perceptible distortions. The use of reinforcement learning and deep neural networks also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.GR (Computer Graphics). The use of reinforcement learning and deep neural networks also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence and machine learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) likely sub-categories as well.
